    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "code": "HV_SUCCESS",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " on success, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "HV_UNSUPPORTED",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " if SME is not supported on the platform, or an error code otherwise.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "You need to call this on the owning thread",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": " For any entry or exit from streaming SVE mode, all Z vector and P predicate registers are set to zero, and all FPSR flags are set; you need to save this state if you need to retain it across streaming SVE mode transitions.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In streaming SVE mode, the system aliases the SIMD Q registers to the bottom ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "128",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " bits of the corresponding Z register, and any modification reflects on the Z register state.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If the optional ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "FEAT_SME_FA64",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " is implemented, the full SIMD instruction set is supported in streaming SVE mode; otherwise many legacy SIMD instructions are illegal in this mode.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When finished, disable streaming SVE mode and ZA storage; this serves as a power-down hint for SME-related hardware.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
